WEBVTT

00:01.202 --> 00:02.836
PREVIOUSLY ON WHITE COLLAR...

00:02.870 --> 00:04.572
NEAL.
ELLEN.

00:04.605 --> 00:05.706
YOU AND YOUR FATHER.

00:05.739 --> 00:07.308
MY MOM TOLD ME
HE WAS DEAD.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.476
BUT YOU
TOLD ME THE TRUTH.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.511
HE WAS A DIRTY COP...
AND HE'S NOT DEAD.

00:10.544 --> 00:13.214
Peter: MS. PARKER, YOU WERE
NEAL'S FATHER'S PARTNER.

00:13.247 --> 00:14.482
THAT'S IT, ISN'T IT?

00:14.515 --> 00:16.984
AGENT BURKE, I'M IN WITSEC
FOR A GOOD REASON.

00:17.017 --> 00:19.487
THESE MARSHALS ARE HERE TO TAKE
NEAL CAFFREY INTO CUSTODY.

00:19.520 --> 00:22.590
HE'LL WORK FOR ME
IN D.C. PERMANENTLY.

00:22.623 --> 00:23.757
YOU BROKE THE RULES.

00:23.791 --> 00:24.758
I GO BACK TO WORK,

00:24.792 --> 00:26.860
AND YOU'RE PLACED UNDER REVIEW
AND REASSIGNED?

00:26.894 --> 00:28.596
I'M SURE
IT'S ONLY TEMPORARY.

00:28.629 --> 00:31.765
Hughes:
IT'S THE EVIDENCE WAREHOUSE,
AND IT'S THE BEST I COULD DO.

00:31.799 --> 00:35.002
THE MARSHALS ARE SHIPPING ME OFF
IN A FEW WEEKS.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.670
EVERYTHING I GREW UP
BELIEVING WAS WRONG,

00:36.704 --> 00:39.073
AND I RAN BEFORE I GOT TO HEAR
THE FULL STORY.

00:39.107 --> 00:40.174
I WANT TO KNOW WHO HE WAS.

00:40.208 --> 00:42.176
WHEN MY DAD WENT AWAY,
ELLEN LOOKED AFTER ME.

00:42.210 --> 00:43.677
YOU GREW UP
IN WITNESS PROTECTION.

00:43.711 --> 00:45.846
I WAS 3 WHEN THE MARSHALS
TOOK US AWAY.

00:45.879 --> 00:46.914
WHAT HAPPENED?

00:46.947 --> 00:48.882
WE FOUND A GUN
WITH HIS PRINTS ON IT.

00:48.916 --> 00:50.184
HE KILLED A COP?

00:50.218 --> 00:51.785
IT WAS A LONG TIME AGO.

00:51.819 --> 00:53.387
I NEED TO KNOW WHO I AM.

01:03.831 --> 01:04.865
AGENT PATTERSON.

01:04.898 --> 01:06.267
WATCHING YOU,
CAFFREY.

01:06.300 --> 01:08.302
ALWAYS GOOD
TO SEE YOU, SIR.

01:08.336 --> 01:10.404
OOH.

01:10.438 --> 01:12.806
PATTERSON'S NOT THE ONLY ONE
KEEPING AN EYE ON ME.

01:12.840 --> 01:15.209
BLACK-MARKET PROSTHETICS
OFF A RAID ON THE DOCKS.

01:15.243 --> 01:17.711
COUNTERFEIT EYEBALLS --
VERY RAT PACK.

01:17.745 --> 01:20.047
HMM?
SAMMY DAVIS JR.
HAD A GLASS EYE.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.549
MM.

01:21.582 --> 01:24.051
WE GOT TO GET YOU BACK
TO WHITE COLLAR.

01:24.084 --> 01:26.287
OH, TELL ME ABOUT IT.
WHAT'S IN THE BAG?

01:26.320 --> 01:28.489
OH, I MADE A DETOUR
ON MY WAY TO THE BANK

01:28.522 --> 01:30.891
TO PICK YOU UP
MANHATTAN'S BEST SANDWICH.

01:30.924 --> 01:32.293
WHY DID YOU GO
TO THE BANK?

01:32.326 --> 01:33.894
YOU DON'T WANT TO KNOW
WHERE I GOT THE SANDWICH?

01:33.927 --> 01:35.263
MARGINALLY
LESS INTERESTING.

01:35.296 --> 01:37.231
FIRST FBI CHECK
SINCE I GOT BACK.

01:37.265 --> 01:38.999
PUT IT IN
MY RAINY-DAY ACCOUNT.

01:39.032 --> 01:40.768
RAINY-DAY ACCOUNT?

01:40.801 --> 01:42.936
WELL, WITH WHAT I GET PAID,
ALL I CAN AFFORD IS AN UMBRELLA.

01:42.970 --> 01:44.071
CUTE.
Sara: GOOD MORNING.

01:44.104 --> 01:45.239
Patterson:
WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

01:45.273 --> 01:46.674
HOW DID YOU LEAVE THINGS
WITH SARA?

01:46.707 --> 01:48.609
NON SEQUITUR. WHY?

01:48.642 --> 01:50.611
LOOK BEHIND YOU.

01:50.644 --> 01:51.979
I'M AN INSURANCE INVESTIGATOR
WITH STERLING-BOSCH.

01:52.012 --> 01:54.582
I'M HERE
TO SEE AGENT BURKE.

01:54.615 --> 01:56.184
SARA.

01:56.217 --> 01:58.652
NEAL. HOW WAS
YOUR ISLAND ADVENTURE?

01:58.686 --> 02:01.589
YOU KNOW, IT WAS
KIND OF LIKE RUM PUNCH.

02:01.622 --> 02:02.956
SEEMED LIKE
A GOOD IDEA AT THE TIME UN--

02:02.990 --> 02:04.525
UNTIL THE HANGOVER?
YEAH.

02:04.558 --> 02:05.959
YEAH. HI, PETER.

02:05.993 --> 02:07.661
SARA. WHAT BRINGS
YOU DOWN HERE?

02:07.695 --> 02:10.264
I'M WORKING
THE COVINGTON SETTLEMENT.

02:10.298 --> 02:12.300
GRANT COVINGTON --
HEDGE FUNDER WE TARGETED

02:12.333 --> 02:14.435
DURING THE SWEEP
ON INSIDER TRADING LAST YEAR.

02:14.468 --> 02:15.969
WE WERE GETTING CLOSE
UNTIL HE DIED.

02:16.003 --> 02:17.605
SCUBA DIVING
IN THE HAMPTONS.

02:17.638 --> 02:20.441
FORFEITURE UNITS
SEIZED ALL ILLEGAL GAINS,

02:20.474 --> 02:21.609
AND WE CLOSED THE CASE.

02:21.642 --> 02:23.611
WELL, I'M CLEANING IT UP
ON OUR END.

02:23.644 --> 02:25.279
HIS DEATH
WAS RULED ACCIDENTAL, SO...

02:25.313 --> 02:27.315
THE YOUNG WIDOW
GETS THE INSURANCE MONEY.

02:27.348 --> 02:29.683
HOW MUCH?
$50 MILLION.

02:29.717 --> 02:31.885
UNLESS I CAN PROVE
SHE DOESN'T DESERVE IT.

02:31.919 --> 02:34.322
NOW, THE NYPD RULED HER OUT
AS A SUSPECT, BUT --

02:34.355 --> 02:36.790
YOU THINK SOPHIE COVINGTON
PULLED ONE OVER ON EVERYONE?

02:36.824 --> 02:39.493
WELL, YOU'RE THE CONNOISSEUR
ON CRIMES OF PERSUASION.

02:39.527 --> 02:40.994
THAT'S WHAT
I WANT YOU TO TELL ME.

02:41.028 --> 02:42.496
AND YOU'RE THE EXPERT
ON THE CASE.

02:42.530 --> 02:44.164
NOW, THERE'S A MEMORIAL
AT 1:00

02:44.198 --> 02:46.133
MARKING THE ANNIVERSARY
OF COVINGTON'S DEATH.

02:46.166 --> 02:47.301
WHO'S UP
FOR A STAKEOUT?

02:47.335 --> 02:49.169
NEAL HAS ERRANDS TO RUN,

02:49.203 --> 02:52.206
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
YOU CAN'T PICK MY BRAIN

02:52.240 --> 02:55.008
OVER MANHATTAN'S
BEST SANDWICH.

02:55.042 --> 02:56.143
THEN I'LL TAKE OVER.

02:56.176 --> 02:57.211
FILL IN.
FILL IN.

02:57.245 --> 02:59.179
THANK YOU.

02:59.213 --> 03:00.881
60 MINUTES, BURKE.

03:00.914 --> 03:02.416
GREAT.

03:07.888 --> 03:10.491
WELL, THE PAPARAZZI
ARE STILL INTERESTED.

03:10.524 --> 03:14.595
A 21-GUN SALUTE --
THAT'S WHAT HIS WILL SAID.

03:14.628 --> 03:17.164
MMM, NICE TO SEE A YEAR
AFTER HIS DEATH,

03:17.197 --> 03:19.066
COVINGTON'S EGO
LIVES ON.

03:19.099 --> 03:21.335
MMM,
THAT IS A GOOD SANDWICH.

03:21.369 --> 03:24.505
NOW THAT THE DEATH CERTIFICATE'S
BEEN ISSUED,

03:24.538 --> 03:27.174
SOPHIE'S GIVING COVINGTON
HIS ELABORATE SEND-OFF.

03:27.207 --> 03:28.776
MAYBE FOR
THE SECOND TIME.

03:28.809 --> 03:31.211
THINK SHE MADE SURE
THAT DIVE WAS HIS LAST?

03:31.245 --> 03:34.448
WELL, SHE CERTAINLY HAD
A LOT TO GAIN FROM HIS DEATH.
MM.

03:34.482 --> 03:37.685
THAT'S WILSON MAILER,
COVINGTON'S HEDGE-FUND PARTNER.

03:37.718 --> 03:39.920
SUSPECTED HE WAS DIRTY, TOO,
BUT NOTHING STUCK.

03:39.953 --> 03:41.755
OHH,
SHE DIDN'T LIKE THAT.

03:41.789 --> 03:44.558
THAT'S A FAMILIAR TOUCH
FOR A MARRIED MAN.

03:44.592 --> 03:47.428
OH, COVINGTON'S ROCKY MARRIAGE
WAS ALL OVER THE GOSSIP RAGS

03:47.461 --> 03:49.263
WHEN WE WERE
INVESTIGATING THEM.

03:49.297 --> 03:50.898
EL LEAVES THEM
IN THE BATHROOM.

03:50.931 --> 03:52.433
HMM.

03:52.466 --> 03:55.235
WELL, PERHAPS THAT'S WHY
SOPHIE'S SO RECLUSIVE.

03:55.269 --> 03:56.437
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
I'VE HAD EYES ON HER

03:56.470 --> 03:58.606
OUTSIDE
OF A BOARDROOM.

03:58.639 --> 04:01.709
HE'S KEEPING
HIS DISTANCE.
YEAH.

04:01.742 --> 04:04.945
HE'S TOO FAR AWAY
TO BE A CURIOUS BYSTANDER

04:04.978 --> 04:07.214
AND TOO SUBTLE
TO BE PAPARAZZI.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.683
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

04:11.352 --> 04:13.421
NEAL,
YOU'VE HARDLY SAID A WORD.

04:13.454 --> 04:14.622
ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE UP FOR THIS?

04:14.655 --> 04:16.590
ELLEN AGREED TO HELP ME
LOOK INTO MY FATHER

04:16.624 --> 04:18.426
BEFORE SHE DISAPPEARS
INTO WITSEC AGAIN.

04:18.459 --> 04:21.562
IT'S NOW OR NEVER.
THERE SHE IS.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.731
HELLO.
HOW ARE YOU?

04:23.764 --> 04:25.399
GOOD.
GOOD.

04:25.433 --> 04:26.567
AFTER ALL THIS TIME,

04:26.600 --> 04:28.802
I THOUGHT YOU TWO
SHOULD KNOW EACH OTHER.

04:28.836 --> 04:30.103
YOU MUST BE MOZZIE.

04:30.137 --> 04:31.672
CHARMED.
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:31.705 --> 04:33.441
IS IT SAFE
FOR YOU OUT HERE?

04:33.474 --> 04:37.445
OH, AS FAR AS ANYONE'S
CONCERNED, I'M, UH, LONG GONE.

04:37.478 --> 04:40.348
UH, WILD GUESS --
BOTH OF THEM ARE NAMED MARSHAL.

04:40.381 --> 04:42.450
BEFORE I LEAVE TOWN,

04:42.483 --> 04:45.185
I THINK IT'S TIME YOU MET
MY OLD FRIEND SAM.

04:45.218 --> 04:48.121
I CONTACTED HIM
AFTER WE TALKED LAST.

04:48.155 --> 04:50.758
SAM?
DID HE KNOW MY FATHER?

04:50.791 --> 04:54.161
HE DID. HE'S A COP --
UNDERCOVER FOR A LONG TIME.

04:54.194 --> 04:55.629
A HARD GUY
TO GET HOLD OF.

04:55.663 --> 04:57.598
WHAT WAS GOING ON
IN MY DEPARTMENT

04:57.631 --> 04:59.433
WAS BIGGER THAN YOUR DAD.

04:59.467 --> 05:03.036
SAM WAS HELPING ME
GET EVIDENCE ON...THE OTHERS.

05:03.070 --> 05:04.772
OTHERS?

05:04.805 --> 05:06.306
WHEN YOUR DAD CONFESSED,
YOU, YOUR MOM, AND I

05:06.340 --> 05:07.508
WERE THROWN INTO WITSEC,

05:07.541 --> 05:09.677
AND THERE WAS NO TIME
TO LOOK FOR ANSWERS.

05:09.710 --> 05:13.280
WORK WITH SAM. MAYBE YOU'LL FIND
WHAT I WANTED TO,

05:13.313 --> 05:15.282
THAT HE WASN'T
A BAD GUY.

05:15.315 --> 05:17.651
I JUST WANT TO
KNOW THE TRUTH.

05:19.753 --> 05:21.622
YOU WANT TO HELP ME
FINISH PLANTING?

05:21.655 --> 05:23.691
I WOULD LOVE TO,
BUT I GOT TO GET BACK TO WORK.

05:23.724 --> 05:26.226
I, ON THE OTHER HAND,
AM KNOWN

05:26.259 --> 05:27.461
FOR MY WORK
WITH YAMADORI BONSAI.

05:27.495 --> 05:28.796
THAT'S TRUE.
[ LAUGHS ]

05:28.829 --> 05:31.632
OH, FORGET-ME-NOTS --
A FITTING AU REVOIR.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.201
LOOK AFTER HER, OKAY?
I WILL.

05:34.234 --> 05:36.136
I'LL SEE YOU SOON.
THANK YOU AGAIN.

05:36.169 --> 05:38.572
YOU'RE A DEAR.

05:38.606 --> 05:40.340
LET ME GET YOU
SOME GLOVES.

05:40.374 --> 05:41.542
OH, SURE.

05:41.575 --> 05:45.479
OUR DELICATE HANDS
ARE ROUGHLY THE SAME SIZE.

05:45.513 --> 05:48.649
WE'RE AT THE SOUTHEAST CORNER
BY THE MONUMENT.

05:48.682 --> 05:50.050
NEAL?

05:50.083 --> 05:52.420
YEP.

05:52.453 --> 05:53.487
[ SIGHS ]

05:53.521 --> 05:55.255
HE SCORCHED
A LOT OF EARTH

05:55.288 --> 05:57.591
WHEN HE LEFT
FOR HIS ISLAND ADVENTURE.

05:57.625 --> 06:00.761
A LITTLE SMOKE DAMAGE HERE,
BUT I WASN'T TOTALLY UNPREPARED.

06:00.794 --> 06:02.430
YOU KNEW
HE WAS GONNA RUN?

06:02.463 --> 06:04.498
SOMETHING I'VE LEARNED --

06:04.532 --> 06:07.568
THINGS GET STOLEN,
AND PEOPLE GO AWAY.

06:07.601 --> 06:10.938
MOST OF THE TIME,
YOU DON'T GET THEM BACK.

06:14.207 --> 06:18.045
DETAIL, ATTENTION!

06:18.078 --> 06:20.748
FORWARD ARMS!

06:20.781 --> 06:22.215
WONDER IF HE GOT A PERMIT
FOR THAT.

06:22.249 --> 06:23.451
YEAH.

06:23.484 --> 06:24.852
MAKE READY! AIM!
[ RIFLES COCK ]

06:24.885 --> 06:29.122
SOPHIE'S LEAVING
BEFORE IT'S OVER.
FIRE!

06:29.156 --> 06:30.524
NOT QUITE
THE GRIEVING WIDOW.

06:30.558 --> 06:32.025
MAKE READY!
[ RIFLES COCK ]

06:32.059 --> 06:35.362
AIM! FIRE!

06:35.395 --> 06:37.397
MAKE READY!

06:37.431 --> 06:39.366
[ RIFLES COCK ]
AIM!

06:39.399 --> 06:41.068
FIRE!

06:42.836 --> 06:44.905
MAKE READY!
[ RIFLES COCK ]

06:44.938 --> 06:47.107
AIM! FIRE!

06:48.609 --> 06:50.878
[ RIFLES COCK ]

06:50.911 --> 06:52.913
FIRE!

06:53.914 --> 06:55.082
[ GASPS ]
FIRE!

06:57.417 --> 06:59.052
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

06:59.086 --> 07:00.888
[ GRUNTS ]

07:00.921 --> 07:03.090
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

07:04.625 --> 07:06.894
I THINK YOU JUST
SAVED MY LIFE.

07:06.927 --> 07:09.062
YOU COULD BE RIGHT.
YOU OKAY?

07:09.096 --> 07:10.230
Man: SOPHIE, OVER HERE!
Man #2: WAIT UP, SOPHIE!

07:10.263 --> 07:12.165
I HAVE TO GO.
I HAVE TO GO.

07:12.199 --> 07:13.734
HEY! WAIT A SECOND!

07:13.767 --> 07:15.503
THIS WAY, MA'AM.
COME ON.
SOPHIE, EXCUSE ME!

07:15.536 --> 07:17.437
STAY BACK!

07:17.471 --> 07:19.339
HEY, YOU ALL RIGHT?
WHAT HAPPENED?

07:19.372 --> 07:20.941
SOMEBODY TRIED
TO GRAB SOPHIE.

07:20.974 --> 07:21.842
[ SIGHS ]

07:21.875 --> 07:23.611
LOOKS LIKE
YOUR INSURANCE-FRAUD CASE

07:23.644 --> 07:25.312
JUST TURNED
ATTEMPTED KIDNAPPING.

07:25.345 --> 07:27.247
WELL, YOU CAN ADD THEFT
TO THAT LIST.

07:27.280 --> 07:30.618
SHE STOLE MY HAT.

07:47.334 --> 07:49.803
SOMETHING DIDN'T SEEM RIGHT,
SO WE GOT OUT OF THE CAR.

07:49.837 --> 07:52.305
I SAW NEAL START TO RUN,
GOT THERE AS FAST AS I COULD,

07:52.339 --> 07:53.941
BUT THE GUY WAS GONE.

07:53.974 --> 07:58.278
IT WAS A FADED BLUE,
GRAYISH VAN -- NO PLATES.

07:58.311 --> 07:59.613
THAT'S ALL I SAW.

07:59.647 --> 08:02.182
REPORTERS CAPTURED
A FEW PHOTOS OF CAFFREY'S HAT,

08:02.215 --> 08:03.383
BUT NOTHING WE CAN USE.

08:03.416 --> 08:07.855
IT ALL HAPPENED TOO FAST.
THANKS, PETER.

08:07.888 --> 08:09.657
YEP.

08:18.431 --> 08:20.801
YOU'LL BE BACK,

08:20.834 --> 08:22.636
SHOUTING DOWN AT US
LIKE ALEXANDER THE GREAT.

08:22.670 --> 08:25.873
I SEE MYSELF
MORE AS A CAESAR.

08:25.906 --> 08:28.642
YOU SAY ROMAN.
I SAY GREEK.

08:28.676 --> 08:29.877
BURKE,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

08:29.910 --> 08:32.079
JUST GAVE DIANA
MY STATEMENT.

08:32.112 --> 08:33.013
THE COVINGTON WIDOW.

08:33.046 --> 08:34.648
KIDNAPPINGS
ARE USUALLY PERSONAL.

08:34.682 --> 08:36.016
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.
WE SHOULD SEND SOMEBODY
OUT THERE WHO KNOWS EVERY--

08:36.049 --> 08:37.517
CAFFREY,
GIVE US A MINUTE, PLEASE.

08:37.551 --> 08:40.487
PETER, JUSTICE IS STILL
REVIEWING YOUR CASE.

08:40.520 --> 08:42.022
COVINGTON IS
AN ACTIVE INVESTIGATION.

08:42.055 --> 08:43.256
YOU NEED TO BACK OFF.

08:43.290 --> 08:45.893
I WAS LEAD ON THAT INVESTIGATION
FOR A YEAR.
I KNOW.

08:45.926 --> 08:49.362
I COULD CONSULT OUTSIDE MY HOURS
AT THE EVIDENCE WAREHOUSE.

08:49.396 --> 08:51.531
NO INVESTIGATING,
NO FIELD WORK.

08:51.565 --> 08:53.066
TAP ME LIKE A GEYSER.

08:53.100 --> 08:56.970
I'LL MAKE A CALL
AS LONG AS YOU KEEP IT TO THAT.

08:58.706 --> 09:00.674
YOU SAID YOU WERE GONNA
MAKE A CALL.

09:00.708 --> 09:02.075
YOU WANT ME
TO DO IT RIGHT NOW?

09:02.109 --> 09:03.043
I'D APPRECIATE THAT.

09:05.946 --> 09:08.716
WHY WERE YOU
LEAVING THE MEMORIAL?

09:08.749 --> 09:10.383
I WAS OVERWHELMED.

09:10.417 --> 09:12.519
MY DRIVER HAD THE CAR
WAITING AROUND THE CORNER.

09:12.552 --> 09:14.855
WHO RUNS AFTER
NEARLY BEING KIDNAPPED?

09:14.888 --> 09:16.556
SOMEONE WHO FEELS LIKE
THEY'RE BEING CHASED.

09:16.590 --> 09:19.727
FIGURES YOU'D SIDE
WITH THE FLEEING SUSPECT.

09:19.760 --> 09:23.964
YOU KNOW, THE THING
ABOUT FLEEING SUSPECTS IS,

09:23.997 --> 09:27.367
THEY CAN'T SAY GOOD BYE...
TO ANYONE.

09:27.400 --> 09:29.536
WELL,
THAT'S ON THE LAM 101.

09:29.569 --> 09:31.872
YOU KNOW WHY
I HAD TO RUN.

09:31.905 --> 09:32.806
I DO.

09:32.840 --> 09:34.141
AND JUST SO YOU KNOW,

09:34.174 --> 09:36.877
THE WORLD DID NOT
STOP SPINNING WITHOUT YOU.

09:36.910 --> 09:38.779
MISS COVINGTON,
I KNOW IT'S BEEN A ROUGH DAY,

09:38.812 --> 09:40.580
BUT WE DO WANT TO HELP YOU.

09:40.614 --> 09:42.716
DO YOU?

09:42.750 --> 09:44.985
WHEN THE FBI
INVESTIGATED MY HUSBAND,

09:45.018 --> 09:47.054
MY LIFE
WAS TURNED INSIDE OUT.

09:47.087 --> 09:49.389
AFTER HE DIED, THAT WRETCHED
INSURANCE INVESTIGATOR

09:49.422 --> 09:52.392
ALL BUT ACCUSED ME
OF MURDER.

09:52.425 --> 09:53.727
THINK SHE'S
TALKING ABOUT YOU?

09:53.761 --> 09:54.962
I'VE HEARD WORSE.

09:54.995 --> 09:56.630
WE'RE ALL JUST TRYING
TO DO OUR JOBS HERE.

09:56.664 --> 09:58.065
YOU'LL HAVE TO EXCUSE ME,

09:58.098 --> 10:00.600
BUT I'VE HAD MY FILL
OF LAW-ENFORCEMENT TYPES.

10:00.634 --> 10:02.736
HEY, DON'T YOU NEED
TO GET BACK TO EVIDENCE?

10:02.770 --> 10:04.638
CONVINCED THE BRASS
TO LET ME CONSULT

10:04.672 --> 10:05.973
ON ALL THINGS COVINGTON.

10:06.006 --> 10:07.741
THEY MADE YOU
A CONSULTANT?
MM-HMM.

10:07.775 --> 10:09.777
DO YOU HAVE A RADIUS?
I HAVE A BADGE.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.912
ONE LAST QUESTION --

10:11.945 --> 10:13.781
WHAT IS THE NATURE
OF YOUR RELATIONSHIP

10:13.814 --> 10:16.316
WITH WILL MAILER?

10:18.385 --> 10:23.156
YOU DO NOT GET TO ASK ME
ABOUT MY PERSONAL LIFE.

10:23.190 --> 10:26.259
OOH, TOUCHY SUBJECT.
CAN I SEE THAT?

10:26.293 --> 10:28.829
ANY MORE QUESTIONS,
YOU CAN CONTACT MY LAWYER.

10:28.862 --> 10:33.466
AND CALL OFF YOUR TAIL.
I'M SICK OF BEING FOLLOWED.

10:33.500 --> 10:34.702
WE DON'T HAVE SURVEILLANCE
ON HER.

10:34.735 --> 10:36.169
NEITHER DOES
STERLING-BOSCH.

10:36.203 --> 10:38.672
THAT GUY WE SAW
LURKING AROUND THE MEMORIAL --

10:38.706 --> 10:40.674
HE'S GOT TO BE INVOLVED.

10:40.708 --> 10:42.776
SOPHIE'S DONE
WITH THE FBI.

10:42.810 --> 10:46.179
OH, BUT I BET SHE WOULD TALK
WITH THE DASHING STRANGER

10:46.213 --> 10:47.180
THAT SAVED HER LIFE.

10:47.214 --> 10:48.615
YEAH, I COULD FIND OUT
WHAT'S REALLY GOING ON

10:48.648 --> 10:49.983
BETWEEN HER
AND MAILER.

10:50.017 --> 10:52.619
IF SOMEONE IS TAILING HER,
WE CAN GET A LOOK.

10:52.652 --> 10:53.887
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

10:53.921 --> 10:56.356
COME WITH ME.
OKAY.

10:56.389 --> 10:58.625
ALL RIGHT, YOU SURE
SHE WON'T RECOGNIZE YOU

10:58.658 --> 11:00.493
FROM YOUR INVESTIGATION
INTO HER HUSBAND?

11:00.527 --> 11:02.562
WE NEVER MET
IN PERSON.

11:02.595 --> 11:05.065
ALL RIGHT, SET ME UP.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:05.098 --> 11:06.867
I HOPE THIS WASN'T
TOO DISRUPTIVE.

11:06.900 --> 11:10.170
OH, IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.
I'M JUST HAPPY I COULD HELP OUT.

11:10.203 --> 11:11.471
IT'S YOU.

11:11.504 --> 11:13.173
HEY.
HI.

11:13.206 --> 11:14.341
YOU OKAY?

11:14.374 --> 11:16.376
I WAS JUST GIVING MY STATEMENT
TO AGENT BURKE HERE.

11:16.409 --> 11:19.579
YES, THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME,
MR...ARMSTRONG.

11:19.612 --> 11:20.981
UH, NEAL.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.916
WELL, AT LEAST NOW
I KNOW YOUR NAME.

11:22.950 --> 11:25.185
YEAH.
NEAL ARMSTRONG.

11:25.218 --> 11:26.019
LIKE THE ASTRONAUT.

11:26.053 --> 11:28.088
ONE SMALL STEP
FOR MAN.

11:28.121 --> 11:30.423
SOPHIE COVINGTON.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

11:30.457 --> 11:32.259
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO THANK YOU
FOR WHAT YOU DID.

11:32.292 --> 11:34.394
IF THERE'S EVER ANYTHING
THAT I CAN DO,

11:34.427 --> 11:36.063
JUST PLEASE LET ME KNOW.

11:36.096 --> 11:39.432
ACTUALLY, THERE IS.
CAN I GET MY HAT BACK?

11:39.466 --> 11:40.834
I DON'T HAVE IT HERE.

11:40.868 --> 11:42.202
WE COULD MEET
FOR COFFEE OR...

11:48.208 --> 11:51.678
THIS IS MY ADDRESS.
COME BY AROUND 4:00.

11:51.711 --> 11:53.213
AND I'LL HAVE IT
WAITING FOR YOU.

11:53.246 --> 11:54.514
ALL RIGHT.

11:54.547 --> 11:58.085
IF I CAN HELP YOU IN ANY WAY,
PLEASE GIVE ME A CALL.

11:58.118 --> 12:00.420
HE'S ONE
OF THE GOOD GUYS.

12:05.625 --> 12:07.194
ARE YOU --

12:07.227 --> 12:09.696
ONE MORE THING
TO DISCUSS WITH AGENT BURKE.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.899
SEE YOU AT 4:00.
BYE.

12:12.833 --> 12:14.434
NEAL ARMSTRONG?

12:14.467 --> 12:15.936
WELL, UH,
ARMS, ARMS --

12:15.969 --> 12:17.771
ALL THOSE PROSTHETICS
IN THE EVIDENCE WAREHOUSE.

12:17.805 --> 12:21.608
A-AT LEAST IT'S BETTER
THAN NEAL HANDLEMAN.

12:21.641 --> 12:23.877
NO, IT'S NOT.
I LIKE NEAL HANDLEMAN.

12:23.911 --> 12:27.414
I SHOULD HAVE GONE
WITH EYES-ENHAUER.

12:27.447 --> 12:29.082
THAT WOULD
HAVE BEEN GOOD.

12:38.758 --> 12:40.727
Tony:
THIS IS MR. MAILER.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.896
JUST HERE
TO PICK UP MY HAT.

12:42.930 --> 12:45.098
AH, THE KNIGHT
IN SHINING ARMOR.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:45.132 --> 12:47.935
MORE OF A RIGHT PLACE,
RIGHT TIME KIND OF THING.

12:49.202 --> 12:51.905
MR. ARMSTRONG,
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.

12:51.939 --> 12:55.075
CALL ME NEAL, PLEASE.

12:55.108 --> 12:58.912
NEAL, IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:58.946 --> 13:01.949
GOOD-BYE, WILL.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.458
HOPE I'M NOT
INTERRUPTING.

13:11.491 --> 13:13.593
I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU'D HAVE A FRIEND OVER.

13:13.626 --> 13:15.195
WILL'S NOT A FRIEND.

13:15.228 --> 13:17.464
HE WAS MY HUSBAND'S
BUSINESS PARTNER.

13:17.497 --> 13:19.867
OH.

13:22.235 --> 13:24.304
SO, TELL ME, NEAL,
ARE YOU A PROFESSIONAL

13:24.337 --> 13:26.206
KIDNAPPING
INTERVENTIONIST OR...

13:26.239 --> 13:28.842
[ LAUGHS ]
NO, I'M AN ENTREPRENEUR.

13:28.876 --> 13:30.277
I'VE DONE WELL
OVER THE YEARS,

13:30.310 --> 13:32.479
AND I ENJOY FINDING
WORTHY CAUSES TO GIVE BACK TO.

13:32.512 --> 13:35.448
I USED TO TEACH PUBLIC SCHOOL.
I -- AFTER I MET GRANT,

13:35.482 --> 13:37.851
I STARTED A CHARITY
FOR ART PROGRAMS.

13:37.885 --> 13:40.120
THE MORE I MADE,
THE MORE I GAVE AWAY,

13:40.153 --> 13:42.055
WHICH WAS JUST SOMETHING ELSE
FOR US TO FIGHT ABOUT.

13:42.089 --> 13:44.124
YOU HAVE A BEAUTIFUL HOME.

13:44.157 --> 13:47.160
THANK YOU.
I SPEND A LOT OF TIME HERE.

13:47.194 --> 13:49.029
THE MEDIA ATTENTION,
IT'S JUST --

13:49.062 --> 13:50.397
WHY YOU TOOK MY HAT.

13:50.430 --> 13:54.167
YES, THAT'S WHY
I TOOK YOUR HAT.
[ LAUGHS ]

13:58.171 --> 14:00.307
HMM, VINTAGE.
YEAH.

14:00.340 --> 14:03.343
I ALMOST HATE
TO GIVE IT BACK.

14:05.712 --> 14:07.047
OH, NICE.
[ LAUGHS ]

14:10.250 --> 14:12.652
THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

14:12.685 --> 14:15.222
SPEAKING OF VINTAGE,
UM...

14:15.255 --> 14:17.657
WOULD YOU LIKE
A GLASS OF WINE OR...

14:17.690 --> 14:19.159
I'D LOVE ONE.

14:19.192 --> 14:20.460
OKAY.

14:23.363 --> 14:27.267
I BACKPACKED THE COSTA BRAVA
AFTER COLLEGE.

14:27.300 --> 14:29.069
THIS RIOJA
REMINDS ME OF IT.

14:35.875 --> 14:38.345
TO SPANISH WINE.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.613
TO HATS.

14:55.795 --> 14:57.697
SO, HOW DOES THIS COUNT
AS CONSULTING?

14:57.730 --> 14:59.466
CONFIRMING I.D.

14:59.499 --> 15:04.037
THAT'S THE SAME GUY
I SAW AT THE MEMORIAL.

15:04.071 --> 15:06.506
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

15:11.344 --> 15:13.646
YOU KNOW, I FEEL LIKE
I'M BEING FOLLOWED.

15:13.680 --> 15:15.282
YEAH,
WE'RE TAILING YOUR TAIL.

15:15.315 --> 15:17.217
Lose him so we can
follow him home.

15:17.250 --> 15:19.252
YOU'RE ASKING ME
TO GIVE UP TRADE SECRETS?

15:19.286 --> 15:21.254
CALL YOUR
PATENT LAWYER.

15:49.682 --> 15:51.451
[ DOOR OPENS ]

15:58.658 --> 15:59.859
JUST A MINUTE.

15:59.892 --> 16:01.428
[ SHOTGUN COCKS ]

16:01.461 --> 16:04.164
ONE SECOND.

16:11.571 --> 16:14.441
GUN! FBI! FBI!

16:14.474 --> 16:15.342
DON'T HURT ME!

16:15.375 --> 16:16.876
CALM DOWN, OR YOU'RE
GONNA HURT YOURSELF!

16:16.909 --> 16:17.977
OKAY, OKAY.

16:24.317 --> 16:26.386
FREDDY SLAVKIN,
WHAT WERE YOU DOING

16:26.419 --> 16:27.987
AT THE COVINGTON MEMORIAL
TODAY?

16:28.021 --> 16:29.956
SOMEONE HIRE YOU
TO GRAB SOPHIE?

16:29.989 --> 16:31.624
DIDN'T GET THE JOB DONE,

16:31.658 --> 16:34.061
SO YOU THOUGHT THEY WERE
COMING AFTER YOU?
WHAT? NO. NO, NO, NO.

16:34.094 --> 16:36.129
SO YOU USUALLY
ANSWER THE DOOR LIKE THAT?

16:36.163 --> 16:39.132
I THOUGHT I WAS DEALING
WITH DISGRUNTLED HUSBANDS.

16:39.166 --> 16:42.235
YOU DON'T STRIKE ME
AS THE ROMANTIC TYPE. EXPLAIN.

16:42.269 --> 16:43.703
I'M A P.I.
I WORK INFIDELITY CASES.

16:43.736 --> 16:45.338
A LOT OF WHAT I FIND TENDS
TO MAKE PEOPLE WANT TO KILL ME.

16:45.372 --> 16:47.074
WHO HIRED YOU
TO TAIL SOPHIE?

16:49.008 --> 16:51.978
YOU PULLED A WEAPON
ON A FEDERAL AGENT.

16:52.011 --> 16:55.982
YOU ARE WAY PAST
CLIENT CONFIDENTIALITY.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.750
WOMAN NAMED
POPPY MAILER.

16:57.784 --> 16:59.052
MAILER'S WIFE.

16:59.086 --> 17:00.320
SHE HIRED YOU TO FIND OUT

17:00.353 --> 17:01.721
IF HE'S HAVING AN AFFAIR
WITH SOPHIE COVINGTON.

17:01.754 --> 17:02.889
Jones: IS HE?

17:02.922 --> 17:05.192
UH, SPENT SIX MONTHS
TRYING TO CONFIRM,

17:05.225 --> 17:07.694
BUT SO FAR ZIP.

17:07.727 --> 17:08.661
MRS. MAILER'S OBSESSED.

17:08.695 --> 17:10.897
SHE WANTS TO KNOW
EVERYTHING ABOUT SOPHIE.

17:10.930 --> 17:12.732
WHO COMES, WHO GOES --
SHE WANTS IT ALL.

17:12.765 --> 17:14.501
YOU TAKE ANY PHOTOS TODAY?
T-THEY'RE IN THE PRINTER.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.669
I HAVEN'T
GONE THROUGH THEM YET.

17:16.703 --> 17:19.606
OLD-SCHOOL.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.679
YOU GOT A SHOT
OF THE KIDNAPPER.

17:26.713 --> 17:29.516
GOOD THING WE'RE
COLLECTING EVIDENCE TODAY.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.184
I NEED EVERYTHING YOU HAVE
ON SOPHIE COVINGTON.

17:31.218 --> 17:33.920
O-OVER THERE.

17:33.953 --> 17:35.555
ALL THAT AND NO PROOF
OF AN AFFAIR,

17:35.588 --> 17:37.590
AND SHE STILL KEEPS YOU
ON RETAINER.

17:37.624 --> 17:39.226
ME AND HER PSYCHIC.

17:47.300 --> 17:49.902
Elizabeth: SOPHIE COVINGTON --
WHAT IS SHE LIKE?

17:49.936 --> 17:51.037
FROM WHAT I SAW,

17:51.070 --> 17:52.772
SHE'S NOT INTO MURDER,
MONEY, OR MAILER.

17:52.805 --> 17:53.873
SO SHE'S NOT
THE GOLD-DIGGING,

17:53.906 --> 17:55.875
SOCIAL-CLIMBING HUSBAND MURDERER
THAT I READ ABOUT?

17:55.908 --> 17:58.411
NO.
I THINK SHE'S LONELY.

17:58.445 --> 18:00.647
WELL, SHE'S NOT A SHOPPER,
BUT MAILER IS.

18:02.515 --> 18:04.551
HANDBAGS,
JEWELRY, FLOWERS.

18:04.584 --> 18:07.220
BIG SPENDER
FOR A GUY WHO'S LOW ON MONEY.

18:07.254 --> 18:08.455
MAILER'S CELL PHONE --

18:08.488 --> 18:10.757
HE CALLS SOPHIE,
BUT SHE DOESN'T CALL BACK.

18:10.790 --> 18:15.162
ALL RIGHT, THESE ARE SOPHIE'S
MOVEMENTS AT THE MEMORIAL.

18:15.195 --> 18:17.297
SOPHIE GETS THERE.
MAILER'S WAITING.

18:17.330 --> 18:20.167
HE TOUCHES HER. SHE PULLS AWAY.
SHE LEAVES.

18:20.200 --> 18:22.269
I DON'T SEE MAILER
ANYWHERE OVER HERE.

18:22.302 --> 18:24.904
HE'S IN THE EARLIER SHOTS
BUT NOT THE LATER ONES.

18:24.937 --> 18:29.742
BECAUSE
HE'S OUR KIDNAPPER.

18:29.776 --> 18:33.180
FROM FREDDY'S FILE,
SAME RED STRIPE ON THE GLOVE.

18:33.213 --> 18:34.447
ALL RIGHT,
NOT DEFINITIVE,

18:34.481 --> 18:36.416
BUT WHAT IF
MAILER AND COVINGTON

18:36.449 --> 18:38.651
RAN THEIR INSIDER-TRADING
SCHEME TOGETHER?

18:38.685 --> 18:40.487
FBI's CLOSING IN,

18:40.520 --> 18:42.121
SO MAILER PINS IT ALL
ON COVINGTON.

18:42.155 --> 18:44.924
SABOTAGED HIS DIVING EQUIPMENT
AND KILLS HIM.

18:44.957 --> 18:47.594
BUT HE REALIZES SOPHIE'S
GONNA GET THE INSURANCE PAYOUT,

18:47.627 --> 18:48.861
SO HE SEDUCES HER.

18:48.895 --> 18:50.129
SHE'S NOT HAVING IT.

18:50.163 --> 18:53.766
HE DECIDES TO GRAB HER
AT THE MEMORIAL. WHY?

18:53.800 --> 18:55.635
HE COULD FORCE HER
TO TRANSFER THE MONEY
TO AN OFFSHORE ACCOUNT.

18:55.668 --> 18:57.103
PAY HER OWN RANSOM.

18:57.136 --> 18:58.371
IT'S BASICALLY
A WHITE-COLLAR MUGGING.

18:58.405 --> 19:00.607
SOPHIE WOULDN'T HAVE
GOTTEN OUT OF THAT VAN ALIVE.

19:00.640 --> 19:02.442
MAILER WAS
AT HER PLACE TODAY.

19:02.475 --> 19:05.178
IF WE'RE RIGHT,
HE'S GONNA TRY AGAIN.
MM-HMM.

19:05.212 --> 19:07.046
SOPHIE LIKES YOU.

19:07.079 --> 19:11.218
IF MAILER THINKS SOMEONE ELSE
IS GOING TO STEAL THAT FORTUNE

19:11.251 --> 19:12.385
BEFORE HE DOES --
NO, NO, NO.

19:12.419 --> 19:14.287
I'M NOT THAT GUY.
I CAN'T CON A WIDOW.

19:14.321 --> 19:16.489
YOU CAN
IF IT'S TO SAVE HER.

19:16.523 --> 19:19.359
WE FORCE MAILER TO ACT,
AND WE NAIL HIM.

19:19.392 --> 19:21.194
WELL, HOW DO WE CONVINCE HIM
THAT WE'RE AN ITEM?

19:21.228 --> 19:22.629
FREDDY.
GOOD.

19:22.662 --> 19:25.465
FREDDY TAKES INCRIMINATING
PHOTOS OF YOU AND SOPHIE.

19:25.498 --> 19:28.134
MRS. MAILER WILL NOT BE
ABLE TO RESIST USING THOSE

19:28.167 --> 19:30.337
TO TURN THE SCREWS
ON HER HUSBAND.

19:30.370 --> 19:33.473
COME ON. IT'S WHAT WE PAY YOU
THE RAINY-DAY BUCKS FOR.

19:33.506 --> 19:34.907
HMM.

19:39.779 --> 19:43.182
[ HORN BLARES ]

19:43.216 --> 19:44.984
COME ON, INFORMATION.

19:45.017 --> 19:46.519
I TOLD YOU,
HE'S UNIQUE.

19:46.553 --> 19:48.888
SO IS BOB SAGET.
THAT TELLS ME NOTHING.

19:48.921 --> 19:51.591
OH.
HEY.

19:51.624 --> 19:53.860
MOZZIE INVITED ME OVER
TO PLAY CARDS.

19:53.893 --> 19:57.163
THAT EXPLAINS THE MARSHALS
TRYING TO BLEND IN OUT FRONT.

19:57.196 --> 19:59.499
ELLEN HAS SO LITTLE TIME
LEFT IN THE CITY,

19:59.532 --> 20:01.401
I THOUGHT SHE SHOULD
SPEND IT WITH FRIENDS.

20:01.434 --> 20:02.502
AWW.

20:02.535 --> 20:05.071
THAT'S AWFULLY CHARITABLE OF YOU
FOR A WEEKDAY.

20:05.104 --> 20:06.506
WELL, I DO HAVE
ULTERIOR MOTIVES.

20:06.539 --> 20:09.776
I WANT TO KNOW MORE
ABOUT YOU AS A CHILD.

20:09.809 --> 20:10.943
I'M NOT TALKING.

20:10.977 --> 20:15.448
COME ON, GIVE ME SOMETHING.
HE FORGED HIS SCHOOL I.D.

20:15.482 --> 20:19.452
HE, UH, CONNED THE BULLIES
OUT OF THEIR MILK MONEY.

20:19.486 --> 20:22.054
WORE TIES TO PRESCHOOL.
[ LAUGHS ]

20:22.088 --> 20:26.726
NO TIES, BUT THERE WAS ALWAYS
A LITTLE CON MAN IN HIM.

20:26.759 --> 20:28.461
Mozzie: I KNEW THAT.

20:28.495 --> 20:31.431
TALENT LIKE HIS IS BORN.
IT'S NOT MADE.

20:31.464 --> 20:32.899
COME ON,
A "FOR INSTANCE."

20:32.932 --> 20:37.570
OKAY, NEAL LOVED SCHOOL,
BUT HIS MOTHER WASN'T, UH --

20:37.604 --> 20:41.073
PUNCTUAL.
SHE WAS A MESS.

20:41.107 --> 20:43.376
SHE NEVER GOT ME
TO SCHOOL ON TIME.

20:43.410 --> 20:45.878
SO, FIRST, HE BROKE IN
AND ADJUSTED THE SCHOOL CLOCK

20:45.912 --> 20:48.047
SO THAT CLASS
STARTED 30 MINUTES LATER.

20:48.080 --> 20:49.282
[ LAUGHS ]

20:49.316 --> 20:51.217
MIND YOU, THIS WAS
WHEN HE WAS IN SECOND GRADE.

20:51.250 --> 20:53.553
OKAY, THAT COULD NOT
HAVE WORKED.

20:53.586 --> 20:55.555
NO, IT DIDN'T.
[ LAUGHS ]

20:55.588 --> 20:57.790
SO THEN HE TRIED
BARRICADING THE ROADS

20:57.824 --> 21:00.560
AND REROUTING THE SCHOOL BUS
TO RUN PAST HIS HOUSE.

21:00.593 --> 21:02.429
THAT ACTUALLY WORKED
FOR A FEW DAYS.

21:02.462 --> 21:03.630
THEN HE GOT SMART

21:03.663 --> 21:06.933
AND STARTED FORGING
HIS OWN CITY BUS PASSES.

21:06.966 --> 21:08.568
I WAS NEVER
LATE AGAIN.

21:08.601 --> 21:09.436
HMM.

21:09.469 --> 21:10.770
OOH, SPEAKING OF,

21:10.803 --> 21:13.940
I CAN'T KEEP
MY SHINING KNIGHTS WAITING.

21:13.973 --> 21:15.508
I SHOULD GO.

21:15.542 --> 21:17.744
GREAT TO SEE YOU.
HMM.

21:17.777 --> 21:20.179
I'LL LET YOU KNOW
WHEN I HEAR FROM SAM, HMM?

21:20.212 --> 21:21.814
OKAY.

21:21.848 --> 21:22.849
BYE-BYE, ELLEN.

21:22.882 --> 21:25.652
BYE, MOZZIE.
THANKS FOR LETTING ME WIN.

21:25.685 --> 21:28.821
SEE YOU SOON.
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:28.855 --> 21:31.257
THANKS, MOZ.

21:31.290 --> 21:32.925
AH,
SHE'S A NICE LADY.

21:32.959 --> 21:34.126
YEAH.

21:34.160 --> 21:35.294
SHE'S REALLY
GONNA MISS NEW YORK.

21:35.328 --> 21:38.197
WE ALL DO.
IT'S A HARD CITY TO LEAVE.

21:38.230 --> 21:41.801
NOW, YOU CAME IN
WITH A SUIT-INDUCED FROWN.

21:41.834 --> 21:44.103
CAN I HELP?
YEAH.

21:44.136 --> 21:46.439
PETER WANTS ME
TO CON A WIDOW.

21:46.473 --> 21:48.441
WELL, WIDOWS FALL
INTO TWO CATEGORIES --

21:48.475 --> 21:50.209
THE BEREAVED
AND THE RELIEVED.

21:50.242 --> 21:52.011
WHICH KIND
DOES HE HAVE YOU DUPING?

21:52.044 --> 21:54.481
THE KIND WITH THE $50-MILLION
BULL'S-EYE ON HER BACK.

21:54.514 --> 21:57.384
SOPHIE COVINGTON?

21:57.417 --> 21:59.686
IS SHE THE KILLER?
NO, SHE'S NOT.

21:59.719 --> 22:01.320
AND I NEED TO
CONVINCE A P.I.

22:01.354 --> 22:03.623
THAT SHE AND I
ARE ROMANTICALLY INVOLVED.

22:03.656 --> 22:06.292
WELL, THAT SHOULDN'T BE
TOO HARD, CHEEKBONES.

22:06.325 --> 22:08.160
DON'T EVER
CALL ME THAT AGAIN.

22:08.194 --> 22:10.229
I WANT YOU TO
TELL THE P.I. WHO I AM,

22:10.262 --> 22:11.364
WHO I'VE ALWAYS BEEN.

22:11.398 --> 22:13.132
A CON MAN?

22:13.165 --> 22:14.233
EXACTLY.

22:14.266 --> 22:15.535
WHILE YOU DO WHAT?

22:17.537 --> 22:19.906
MR. ARMSTRONG.
TONY.

22:26.078 --> 22:27.680
NEAL.

22:27.714 --> 22:30.417
HEY.
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

22:30.450 --> 22:31.651
OH, ALL THAT TALK
OF SPAIN LAST NIGHT

22:31.684 --> 22:33.520
REMINDED ME
OF CADAQUéS --

22:33.553 --> 22:35.488
ROCKY BEACHES,
ARTISTS' COLONIES,

22:35.522 --> 22:37.256
BEST SEAFOOD
I EVER HAD.

22:37.289 --> 22:38.858
THAT IS A PAELLA PAN.

22:38.891 --> 22:41.227
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO GO
TO THE COSTA BRAVA

22:41.260 --> 22:43.062
WITHOUT
LEAVING THE HOUSE?

22:46.132 --> 22:48.535
[ SIGHS ]

22:50.202 --> 22:53.172
FELLOW ORNITHOLOGIST.

22:53.205 --> 22:54.173
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

22:54.206 --> 22:55.675
WHAT KIND OF BIRD
YOU WATCHING?

22:55.708 --> 22:58.411
THE KIND THAT STEALS NEST EGGS
AND FLIES SOUTH REAL FAST.

23:00.880 --> 23:04.917
MAN'S GOT SOMETHING ON HIS MIND
BESIDES THE HAT.

23:04.951 --> 23:05.952
"MALTESE FALCON."

23:05.985 --> 23:08.187
YEAH, YEAH.
UH-HUH.

23:08.220 --> 23:10.122
ALL TRUE.

23:12.559 --> 23:14.627
SO, WHAT WERE YOU DOING
IN CADAQUéS?

23:14.661 --> 23:17.263
JUST PASSING THROUGH
ON MY WAY FROM FRANCE.

23:17.296 --> 23:19.432
FOUND THE DALI MUSEUM
VERY CHALLENGING.

23:19.466 --> 23:20.533
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:20.567 --> 23:23.102
ALL RIGHT.
HOPE YOU'RE HUNGRY.

23:26.238 --> 23:29.208
MMM, MMM!

23:29.241 --> 23:32.311
BEST HALAL CART
IN THE CITY.

23:32.344 --> 23:33.412
WANT?

23:33.446 --> 23:34.747
I'LL TAKE YOUR WORD
FOR IT.

23:34.781 --> 23:35.882
MM.

23:35.915 --> 23:38.651
YOU KNOW, YOUR GUY
JUST STARTED COMING AROUND.

23:38.685 --> 23:40.753
OH, PROBABLY
SMELLS THE GREENBACKS.

23:40.787 --> 23:42.655
YOU MAY HAVE
HEARD OF HIM --

23:42.689 --> 23:45.458
NICK HALDEN,
GEORGE DEVORE...

23:45.492 --> 23:47.860
NEAL ARMSTRONG.

23:49.428 --> 23:50.897
CON MAN.

23:50.930 --> 23:54.266
OH, WORLD CLASS.

23:54.300 --> 23:56.302
THIS IS REALLY NICE.

23:56.335 --> 23:57.904
IT'S ONE
OF MY FAVORITES.

23:57.937 --> 24:00.940
NO, I MEAN THIS --
STAYING IN, MAKING LUNCH.

24:00.973 --> 24:03.576
NEVER DID THAT
WHEN I WAS MARRIED.

24:03.610 --> 24:05.745
YOUR HUSBAND
WASN'T INTO COOKING?

24:05.778 --> 24:09.415
TURNS OUT WE ACTUALLY
DIDN'T HAVE THAT MUCH IN COMMON.

24:09.448 --> 24:11.250
I ADMIT I JUMPED IN
WITHOUT LOOKING,

24:11.283 --> 24:13.620
BUT YOU MAKE A CHOICE
AND --

24:13.653 --> 24:15.488
AND SUDDENLY,
YOU'RE LIVING A LIFE

24:15.522 --> 24:17.156
YOU NEVER THOUGHT
YOU'D HAVE.

24:17.189 --> 24:20.426
BEEN THERE --
A COUPLE TIMES.

24:20.459 --> 24:21.928
THIS THE GALA
FOR YOUR CHARITY?

24:21.961 --> 24:23.095
YEAH.

24:23.129 --> 24:25.164
I WAS GONNA GO,
DONATE THE INSURANCE SETTLEMENT.

24:25.197 --> 24:26.265
ALL OF IT?

24:26.298 --> 24:28.868
I DON'T FEEL RIGHT
HAVING IT,

24:28.901 --> 24:30.436
BUT I'M NOT READY
TO GO BACK OUT THERE,

24:30.469 --> 24:34.040
SO I'LL JUST
SEND A CHECK.

24:34.073 --> 24:37.644
YOU KNOW, NOT LONG AGO,
I TOOK OFF FOR A WHILE.

24:37.677 --> 24:40.780
THOUGHT A BREAK FROM NEW YORK
WAS WHAT I NEEDED.

24:40.813 --> 24:44.450
AND THEN A FRIEND HELPED ME
FIND A WAY TO GET MY LIFE BACK.

24:44.483 --> 24:47.219
WASN'T EASY, BUT...

24:47.253 --> 24:49.488
IT WAS WORTH IT.

24:51.190 --> 24:53.459
I SHOULD GO.

24:53.492 --> 24:55.728
OKAY.
CAN YOU WALK ME OUT?

24:55.762 --> 24:58.097
SURE.

25:06.338 --> 25:08.140
[ SIGHS ]

25:08.174 --> 25:10.142
GUESS THIS
IS GOOD-BYE?

25:10.176 --> 25:12.244
GUESS IT IS.

25:12.278 --> 25:14.681
OKAY.

25:19.619 --> 25:22.154
BYE, SOPHIE.

25:22.188 --> 25:23.222
BYE.

25:32.298 --> 25:33.700
[ LAUGHS ]

25:33.733 --> 25:35.501
FORGET SOMETHING?

25:35.534 --> 25:36.669
OH,
IT LOOKS BETTER ON YOU,

25:36.703 --> 25:38.237
BUT I SHOULD PROBABLY
HANG ON TO IT.

25:38.270 --> 25:40.172
YEAH.

25:40.206 --> 25:42.174
ALL RIGHT.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.110
ALL RIGHT.

25:47.213 --> 25:48.581
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

25:52.819 --> 25:55.054
MUST HAVE BEEN
A HELL OF A PAELLA.

26:05.431 --> 26:07.099
Peter: OOH. MM-HMM.

26:07.133 --> 26:08.534
YEAH, I WENT FOR THE HUG.
SOPHIE UPPED IT TO A KISS.

26:08.567 --> 26:09.736
YEAH, AND YOU COULDN'T
DENY THE KISS

26:09.769 --> 26:10.870
'CAUSE YOU WERE WORKING.

26:10.903 --> 26:12.538
WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO GET THE JOB DONE.

26:12.571 --> 26:13.606
GOOD HUSTLE.
THANK YOU.

26:13.640 --> 26:14.707
WHERE'D YOU GET THESE?

26:14.741 --> 26:16.142
ENVELOPE
ON MY DOORSTEP,

26:16.175 --> 26:18.611
ALONG WITH AN INVOICE
FOR FIVE HOURS OF P.I. WORK

26:18.645 --> 26:19.712
TO BE PAID IN CASH.

26:19.746 --> 26:21.213
HONEST DAY'S WORK
FOR MOZ.

26:21.247 --> 26:22.214
YEAH, FOR A CHANGE.

26:22.248 --> 26:23.149
Diana: HEY.

26:23.182 --> 26:24.751
HEY.

26:24.784 --> 26:26.285
DID YOU SET UP AN AUTO ALERT
ON MAILER'S BANK ACCOUNT?

26:26.318 --> 26:28.921
POPPY WITHDRAWS ANYTHING MORE
THAN 100 BUCKS,

26:28.955 --> 26:30.256
WILL MAILER
GETS A TEXT MESSAGE.

26:30.289 --> 26:31.824
AND?
WORKED LIKE A CHARM.

26:33.125 --> 26:35.261
Jones: WE SET UP SURVEILLANCE
IN FREDDY'S BUILDING.

26:35.294 --> 26:37.730
SHE TOOK OUT MONEY.
HE GOT CURIOUS AND FOLLOWED HER.

26:37.764 --> 26:40.032
THIS GETS GOOD.

26:42.201 --> 26:44.570
Will: POPPY, WHAT THE HELL
IS GOING ON?

26:44.603 --> 26:45.738
Poppy:
YOU FOLLOWED ME?!

26:45.772 --> 26:47.807
YOU ARE GOING THROUGH MONEY
LIKE WATER!

26:47.840 --> 26:49.676
WHY DON'T YOU TAKE A LOOK
AT THIS, WILL?

26:49.709 --> 26:52.745
YOUR WHORE
HAS FOUND HERSELF ANOTHER MAN.

26:52.779 --> 26:53.946
YOU PUT A P.I.
ON SOPHIE?

26:53.980 --> 26:55.314
HOW LONG
HAS THIS BEEN GOING ON?

26:55.347 --> 26:57.583
LONG ENOUGH TO KNOW
WHAT A BASTARD I MARRIED.

26:57.616 --> 26:59.018
YOU KNOW
WHAT THE BEST PART IS?

26:59.051 --> 27:00.486
HAT MAN
IS AFTER HER MONEY.

27:00.519 --> 27:03.856
LOOKS LIKE MOZ
EARNED HIS PAY.

27:03.890 --> 27:05.591
MM-HMM, WHEN HE GETS ME
HIS SOCIAL-SECURITY NUMBER.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.794
MM-HMM.
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

27:09.896 --> 27:12.164
HELLO?

27:12.198 --> 27:14.834
SOPHIE, HI.

27:14.867 --> 27:17.804
I THINK WE'VE FOUND
OUR WIDOW OF OPPORTUNITY.

27:19.638 --> 27:21.273
GET IT?
DROPPED THE "N."

27:21.307 --> 27:22.441
YEAH.

27:22.474 --> 27:24.043
MM, THAT...

27:25.311 --> 27:28.380
SOPHIE INVITED CAFFREY
TO ESCORT HER TO THE GALA.

27:28.414 --> 27:30.016
IT'S ALREADY HIT THE WEBSITES.
MAILER WILL KNOW.

27:30.049 --> 27:31.650
Neal: IF MAILER'S PLAN
IS TO GRAB SOPHIE,

27:31.684 --> 27:33.119
THIS IS HIS CHANCE.

27:33.152 --> 27:35.454
WE'LL HAVE AGENTS
AT ALL POINTS OF ENTRY --

27:35.487 --> 27:37.556
PERIMETER SURROUNDING
THE BUILDING, OUTSIDE HER HOUSE.

27:37.589 --> 27:40.059
IF MAILER MAKES A MOVE,
WE'RE READY.

27:40.092 --> 27:41.627
WE'LL TRACK YOU
IN THE LIMO VIA CELL SIGNAL.

27:41.660 --> 27:43.629
ALL RIGHT, GEAR UP.
HEAD OUT.

27:43.662 --> 27:46.232
JONES, TAKE OFF
CAFFREY'S ANKLET.

27:48.735 --> 27:51.070
Where's Peter?

27:51.103 --> 27:53.305
EVIDENCE.
NOTHING LEFT TO CONSULT ON.

27:53.339 --> 27:55.742
HE SHOULD BE HERE.
DON'T WORRY, CAFFREY --

27:55.775 --> 27:57.309
I'LL BE THERE
TO KEEP AN EYE ON YOU.

27:57.343 --> 28:00.112
EVER TELL YOU
HOW MUCH I HATE THAT VAN?

28:04.183 --> 28:05.117
[ HORN HONKS ]

28:07.519 --> 28:09.488
EVERYONE IN POSITION.

28:09.521 --> 28:10.990
Eyes on Mailer.
Call it in.

28:11.023 --> 28:12.859
THAT MAN
IS NOT HAPPY.

28:12.892 --> 28:14.761
WELL, THE VAN
WILL DO THAT TO YOU.

28:14.794 --> 28:16.863
CAFFREY BETTER BE
ON HIS BEST BEHAVIOR.

28:21.200 --> 28:23.369
CAFFREY'S EN ROUTE.

28:26.806 --> 28:28.074
SORRY I KEPT YOU
WAITING.

28:28.107 --> 28:30.442
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.
YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL.

28:30.476 --> 28:31.911
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:31.944 --> 28:34.113
TONY, HOW ARE
WE DOING FOR TIME?

28:34.146 --> 28:36.749
OH, WE SHOULD BE ALL RIGHT,
MISS COVINGTON.

28:37.917 --> 28:41.120
WHAT'S WRONG?
YOU SEEM DISTRACTED.

28:41.153 --> 28:43.522
I'M ADMIRING
TONY'S WATCH.

28:43.555 --> 28:44.924
THAT THE NEW FATHOM 20?

28:44.957 --> 28:47.193
IT IS.
PRICEY.

28:47.226 --> 28:48.694
WAS IT WORTH IT?

28:48.727 --> 28:50.963
I THINK SO.

28:54.901 --> 28:58.037
YOU THINK I'D LOOK GOOD
WITH A WATCH LIKE TONY'S?

28:58.070 --> 29:00.039
I'M NOT SURE
IT WOULD SUIT YOU?

29:00.072 --> 29:01.707
BUT YOU DON'T REALLY KNOW ME,
DO YOU?

29:01.740 --> 29:03.209
WHY DO YOU THINK
WE MET?

29:03.242 --> 29:05.211
I DON'T KNOW --
HAPPY COINCIDENCE.

29:05.244 --> 29:08.047
OR RESCUING YOU TURNED OUT
TO BE THE PERFECT WAY IN.

29:08.080 --> 29:09.381
IN?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

29:09.415 --> 29:10.549
WHEN I WAS AT YOUR PLACE,

29:10.582 --> 29:12.885
YOU TOLD ME YOU FELT BAD
ABOUT HAVING ALL THAT MONEY.

29:12.919 --> 29:16.755
I WANTED TO HELP.
SO I TOOK IT OFF YOUR HANDS.

29:16.789 --> 29:17.957
YOU TOOK IT?

29:17.990 --> 29:19.625
YOUR BANKING INFORMATION
WASN'T HARD TO FIND.

29:19.658 --> 29:21.427
YOU STOLE $50 MILLION
FROM HER?

29:23.930 --> 29:27.133
YEAH,
THERE IT GOES.

29:27.166 --> 29:30.069
JUST PUT $50 MILLION
INTO MY RAINY-DAY ACCOUNT.

29:30.102 --> 29:32.805
YOU WERE GONNA
GIVE IT AWAY.

29:32.839 --> 29:35.074
TONY,
CALL THE POLICE.

29:35.107 --> 29:36.943
TONY DOESN'T
WORK FOR YOU ANYMORE.

29:36.976 --> 29:38.978
THAT WATCH
MEANS TONY CAN BE BOUGHT.

29:39.011 --> 29:41.080
HE KNOWS HOW
TO FOLLOW THE MONEY.

29:41.113 --> 29:43.215
MAYBE HE WANTS TO
COME WORK FOR ME.

29:44.550 --> 29:45.852
SHE'S GOT A PARTY
TO GET TO.

29:45.885 --> 29:47.820
LET HER OUT.

29:47.854 --> 29:50.756
BY THE TIME YOU CALL
THAT FBI AGENT BURKE,

29:50.789 --> 29:52.091
WE'LL BE LONG GONE.

29:52.124 --> 29:55.928
NO ONE'S
MAKING ANY CALLS.

29:55.962 --> 29:57.096
I'M SORRY,
MISS COVINGTON.

29:57.129 --> 29:58.530
GIVE ME YOUR PHONE
AND GET OUT -- NOW.

29:58.564 --> 29:59.531
WHAT ARE YOU...?

30:08.640 --> 30:09.976
YOU MAKE ME SICK!

30:11.477 --> 30:13.712
WAS ANY OF IT REAL?

30:13.745 --> 30:15.982
GO.

30:21.653 --> 30:23.222
I NEED YOUR PHONE, TOO.

30:29.361 --> 30:31.463
YOU HAVE THE MONEY?

30:31.497 --> 30:32.999
I SAID I DID.

30:33.032 --> 30:35.667
THAT WAS A BAD IDEA.

30:35.701 --> 30:37.536
WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT.

30:50.917 --> 30:53.519
STOP STARING AT ME.

30:53.552 --> 30:55.521
HELP ME GET THROUGH THIS,
WE CAN GO HOME TO THE WIVES.

30:55.554 --> 30:58.991
SCALE OF WORST EVIDENCE
YOU'VE HANDLED, HOW BAD IS THIS?

30:59.025 --> 31:02.861
OH, IT'S NOTHING.
THE SNAKES -- THAT WAS BAD.

31:02.895 --> 31:06.933
I HATE SNAKES.
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

31:06.966 --> 31:08.534
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

31:08.567 --> 31:09.768
PETER BURKE.

31:09.801 --> 31:12.404
AGENT BURKE,
THIS IS SOPHIE COVINGTON.

31:12.438 --> 31:13.872
SOPHIE, YOU ALL RIGHT?

31:13.906 --> 31:16.175
YOU SAID TO CALL YOU
IF I NEEDED HELP.

31:16.208 --> 31:17.944
I NEED HELP.
THE MAN THAT SAVED MY LIFE --

31:17.977 --> 31:20.947
NEAL?
He stole my money.

31:20.980 --> 31:22.915
IS THAT A PERSONAL CALL?

31:22.949 --> 31:24.583
WHERE IS HE NOW?

31:24.616 --> 31:25.751
He's with Tony,
my driver.

31:25.784 --> 31:28.887
THEY -- THEY FORCED ME
OUT OF MY CAR,

31:28.921 --> 31:30.022
and he took my phone.

31:30.056 --> 31:32.791
ALL RIGHT, SOPHIE,
THIS IS VERY IMPORTANT.

31:32.824 --> 31:35.427
WHAT EXACTLY
DID NEAL SAY TO YOU?

31:35.461 --> 31:37.964
HE SAID HE PUT MY HUSBAND'S
LIFE-INSURANCE MONEY

31:37.997 --> 31:40.032
INTO HIS RAINY-DAY ACCOUNT.

31:40.066 --> 31:41.800
HE SAID THAT --
RAINY-DAY ACCOUNT?

31:41.833 --> 31:43.369
HE SAID THAT BY THE TIME
I CALLED YOU,

31:43.402 --> 31:44.203
HE'D BE LONG GONE.

31:44.236 --> 31:45.471
HE MENTIONED ME BY NAME?

31:45.504 --> 31:47.773
That's how I remembered
you'd given me your card.

31:47.806 --> 31:49.375
HE SAID
HE TOOK $50 MILLION,

31:49.408 --> 31:51.310
BUT I DON'T HAVE
THAT MUCH MONEY.

31:51.343 --> 31:55.982
SOPHIE, YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.
STAY WHERE YOU ARE.

31:56.015 --> 31:58.084
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]

32:00.752 --> 32:02.488
WHERE
ARE YOU GOING?

32:04.023 --> 32:05.891
BURKE,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

32:05.924 --> 32:07.826
ONE STEP OUT THAT DOOR,
I WRITE YOU UP.

32:07.859 --> 32:09.895
IT GOES ON YOUR RECORD.

32:09.928 --> 32:12.098
BURKE,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

32:12.131 --> 32:14.633
TO CROSS THE LINE.

32:21.207 --> 32:24.810
SAW A PICTURE OF YOU
WITH SOPHIE COVINGTON.

32:24.843 --> 32:26.778
YOU MOVE FAST.

32:26.812 --> 32:28.780
WHY NOT?
SHE'S A NICE GIRL.

32:28.814 --> 32:31.650
WITH A LOT OF MONEY.
YOU SCREWED ME.

32:31.683 --> 32:32.951
TWICE.

32:32.985 --> 32:35.187
BUT TODAY,
YOU FORGOT YOUR LUCKY HAT.

32:35.221 --> 32:38.257
YOU DON'T NEED LUCK
WHEN YOU GOT A PLAN.

32:38.290 --> 32:40.759
TIME TO TELL ME
WHO THE HELL YOU REALLY ARE.

32:40.792 --> 32:42.594
MY NAME'S
NEAL CAFFREY.

32:42.628 --> 32:44.663
I'M THE BEST THING
THAT EVER HAPPENED TO YOU.

32:46.232 --> 32:49.101
CAFFREY'S SIGNAL'S
STILL NOT UP.

32:49.135 --> 32:51.137
PULL TRAFFIC CAMS
FOR ALL ROUTES

32:51.170 --> 32:53.405
FROM THE
COVINGTON RESIDENCE.
RIGHT AWAY, SIR.

32:54.973 --> 32:57.143
HEY, PETER!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

32:57.176 --> 32:58.844
YOU WEREN'T AUTHORIZED TO --
NEAL IS IN TROUBLE.

32:58.877 --> 33:01.013
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?
ARE YOU TRACKING
HIS PHONE?

33:01.047 --> 33:02.281
WELL, THE SIGNAL DROPPED.
WE'RE WORKING ON IT.

33:02.314 --> 33:05.217
THIS OP'S GONE OFF THE RAILS.
MAILER'S NOT COMING.

33:05.251 --> 33:06.818
HE PAID OFF
SOPHIE'S DRIVER.

33:06.852 --> 33:08.120
SHE AND CAFFREY
BOTH GOT GRABBED?

33:08.154 --> 33:10.122
YEAH, BUT NEAL MANAGED
TO GET HER OUT OF THE CAR.

33:10.156 --> 33:12.891
SOPHIE CALLED ME.
SHE'S SAFE, BUT HE'S ON HIS OWN.

33:12.924 --> 33:14.626
ANY IDEA WHERE HE IS?

33:14.660 --> 33:16.995
NO, BUT I THINK I KNOW
HOW TO GET HIM OUT OF THERE.

33:17.029 --> 33:19.965
THIS WAY.

33:19.998 --> 33:22.701
I THOUGHT IT'D BE BEST
IF YOU FILLED HER IN.

33:22.734 --> 33:23.735
ALL YOURS.

33:23.769 --> 33:26.805
[ SIGHS ]
SOPHIE...

33:26.838 --> 33:29.341
NEAL WORKS
FOR THE FBI.

33:29.375 --> 33:31.643
WE SENT HIM UNDERCOVER
TO PROTECT YOU.

33:31.677 --> 33:34.880
HE SAID THAT HE SIPHONED THE
LIFE-INSURANCE MONEY FROM YOU,

33:34.913 --> 33:35.981
BUT HE DIDN'T.

33:36.014 --> 33:37.983
THEN WHY
WOULD HE SAY THAT?

33:38.016 --> 33:39.251
TO GET YOU
OUT OF THE CAR.

33:39.285 --> 33:40.919
HE FIGURED OUT
TONY HAD BEEN PAID OFF

33:40.952 --> 33:41.920
TO ABDUCT YOU.

33:41.953 --> 33:43.255
PAID OFF BY WHO?

33:43.289 --> 33:45.991
WILSON MAILER
TRIED TO KIDNAP YOU.

33:46.024 --> 33:48.360
HE'S AFTER
THE INSURANCE PAYOUT.

33:48.394 --> 33:49.228
OH, MY GOD.

33:49.261 --> 33:50.429
I GOT HERE
AS FAST AS I COULD.

33:50.462 --> 33:52.098
Hughes: HOW DO WE GET CAFFREY
OUT OF THERE?

33:52.131 --> 33:53.732
HE PASSED ME A MESSAGE
THROUGH SOPHIE.

33:53.765 --> 33:55.667
WE NEED TO PUT
THE ENTIRE INSURANCE SETTLEMENT

33:55.701 --> 33:57.936
IN NEAL'S BANK ACCOUNT.

33:57.969 --> 34:00.506
$25 MILLION
FROM EACH OF YOU.

34:00.539 --> 34:01.873
SURE YOU GOT
THAT MESSAGE RIGHT?

34:01.907 --> 34:03.509
YEAH. I KNOW NEAL.

34:03.542 --> 34:06.678
SARA, I'M SURE YOU CAN
GET AUTHORIZATION FOR THAT.

34:06.712 --> 34:08.547
YOU WANT 15%?

34:08.580 --> 34:10.116
IT'S A GOOD DEAL.

34:10.149 --> 34:11.750
[ LAUGHS ]
FOR YOU.

34:11.783 --> 34:15.354
BETTER DEAL FOR ME
IS KILL YOU AND KEEP ALL OF IT.

34:15.387 --> 34:17.189
I CAN'T TRANSFER THE MONEY
IF I'M DEAD.

34:17.223 --> 34:20.025
YOU KILL ME,
YOU'VE GOT A BODY TO GET RID OF.

34:20.058 --> 34:22.894
I'VE BEEN SEEN WITH SOPHIE.
SHE THINKS I STOLE THE MONEY.

34:22.928 --> 34:24.363
I'M YOUR FACE MAN.

34:24.396 --> 34:26.932
YOU BELIEVE IN LUCK,
YOU CAN PUSH YOURS,

34:26.965 --> 34:28.267
OR YOU PAY ME ENOUGH MONEY
TO DISAPPEAR,

34:28.300 --> 34:30.035
AND IT'S A WIN-WIN.

34:30.068 --> 34:32.538
WHAT KEEPS YOU
FROM TURNING ME IN?

34:32.571 --> 34:34.106
MAY I?

34:45.351 --> 34:49.255
THINK A GUY WITH A WANTED POSTER
IS GONNA GO TO THE LAW?

34:52.090 --> 34:56.061
SO, YOUR PLAN
IS TO PUT $50 MILLION

34:56.094 --> 34:58.464
INTO THE PERSONAL BANK ACCOUNT
OF A CON MAN

34:58.497 --> 34:59.998
WHO RECENTLY FLED
TO A REMOTE ISLAND

35:00.031 --> 35:01.400
WITH NO EXTRADITION?

35:01.433 --> 35:03.469
SO THAT HE CAN TRANSFER IT
TO A FINANCIAL GENIUS

35:03.502 --> 35:05.237
WHO WILL HAVE
MADE EVERY EFFORT

35:05.271 --> 35:06.972
TO MAKE SURE
THAT WE CAN'T TRACE IT.

35:07.005 --> 35:08.974
YEP.

35:09.007 --> 35:11.310
IT'S YOUR MONEY,
LADIES.

35:11.343 --> 35:14.546
HE SAVED MY LIFE.
I'M IN.

35:16.382 --> 35:19.618
Peter:
HE MUST HAVE A PLAN.

35:21.453 --> 35:24.623
10%,
AND YOU HAVE A DEAL.

35:24.656 --> 35:26.124
I CAN WORK WITH THAT.

35:26.158 --> 35:28.294
DO THE TRANSFER.

35:38.637 --> 35:41.106
SARA, IN OR OUT?

35:41.139 --> 35:43.475
OKAY.

35:43.509 --> 35:44.476
I'M IN, TOO.

35:44.510 --> 35:47.346
OKAY.

36:02.494 --> 36:04.796
ALL RIGHT,
TONY'S PAID OFF,

36:04.830 --> 36:06.131
I'M NOT
SAYING ANYTHING,

36:06.164 --> 36:08.334
AND YOU'RE A MUCH RICHER MAN
THAN I AM.

36:08.367 --> 36:10.302
IT'S A PLEASURE
DOING BUSINESS WITH SOMEONE

36:10.336 --> 36:11.637
WHO SETS THE BAR
SO HIGH.

36:11.670 --> 36:13.705
MEANS SOMETHING
COMING FROM YOU.

36:13.739 --> 36:16.141
I GOT TO ASK --
GRANT COVINGTON --

36:16.174 --> 36:18.043
HOW DID YOU
PULL THAT OFF?

36:18.076 --> 36:19.144
OXYGEN TANK?

36:19.177 --> 36:22.080
SWITCHED OUT
THE REGULATOR VALVE.

36:22.113 --> 36:25.651
JUST LIKE THAT,
NOTHING LEFT BEHIND.

36:25.684 --> 36:27.152
IF IT WEREN'T FOR THAT P.I.
AND HIS PHOTOS,

36:27.185 --> 36:30.155
I WOULDN'T HAVE TO RUN.

36:30.188 --> 36:32.157
YOU'VE SEEN THEM,
RIGHT?

36:32.190 --> 36:33.759
THERE ARE
NONE OF YOU?

36:35.894 --> 36:37.429
NOTHING LEFT BEHIND.

36:37.463 --> 36:39.698
GUESS YOU REALLY ARE
A LUCKY MAN.

36:43.469 --> 36:45.404
THINK I COULD GET
MY PHONE BACK?

36:50.242 --> 36:53.011
WE SHOULD HAVE
HEARD FROM HIM BY NOW.

36:53.044 --> 36:54.746
YEAH.

36:54.780 --> 36:56.848
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

36:56.882 --> 36:57.916
AH.

36:58.984 --> 37:00.185
NEAL?

37:00.218 --> 37:02.254
NEAL: Well, the good news is,
I'm alive.

37:02.288 --> 37:04.022
THAT IS GOOD NEWS.

37:04.055 --> 37:05.624
WAIT,
IS THERE BAD NEWS?

37:05.657 --> 37:06.858
DEPENDS ON WHETHER
YOU'RE A "GLASS HALF FULL"

37:06.892 --> 37:08.627
OR A "GLASS HALF EMPTY"
KIND OF PERSON.

37:08.660 --> 37:11.397
YOU LOST HALF THE MONEY?
Or a glass 10% full.

37:11.430 --> 37:13.365
MAILER HAS 90%?!

37:13.399 --> 37:15.200
SOMETIMES IN LIFE,
YOU HAVE TO CUT A DEAL.

37:15.233 --> 37:17.536
ANY OTHER GOOD NEWS?
YEAH.

37:17.569 --> 37:19.037
MAILER'S HEADED TO FREDDY'S
TO DESTROY THE EVIDENCE.

37:19.070 --> 37:20.238
WE DON'T HAVE MUCH TIME.

37:20.939 --> 37:24.543
I SEND YOU,
IT'S BOTH OUR ASSES ON THE LINE.

37:24.576 --> 37:25.677
YEAH.

37:27.513 --> 37:29.581
NEAL,
I'M ON MY WAY.

37:46.131 --> 37:48.667
[ DOOR CREAKS ]

38:01.947 --> 38:03.515
Peter: FBI!

38:03.549 --> 38:06.318
SHOW ME YOUR HANDS.
DROP THE WEAPON.

38:07.553 --> 38:10.422
NICE GLOVES.
THEY LOOK FAMILIAR.

38:10.456 --> 38:12.591
IT'S KIND OF WARM OUT THERE
FOR THOSE, ISN'T IT?

38:12.624 --> 38:16.695
YEAH, IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.
TURN AROUND.

38:23.569 --> 38:27.005
WILSON MAILER,
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

38:29.307 --> 38:31.777
GOOD THING
WE WERE BEHIND THAT DOOR.

38:31.810 --> 38:35.046
GUY WHO LIVES HERE
WOULD HAVE SHOT YOU.

38:40.151 --> 38:42.020
[ TELEPHONES RINGING ]

38:44.690 --> 38:47.325
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

38:54.866 --> 38:57.536
SOPHIE, THE THINGS I SAID
IN THE LIMO --

38:57.569 --> 38:58.970
YOU DON'T NEED
TO APOLOGIZE.

38:59.004 --> 39:03.809
LISTEN, YOU ASKED ME
IF ANY OF IT WAS REAL.

39:03.842 --> 39:05.544
A LOT OF IT WAS.

39:05.577 --> 39:08.146
[ SIGHS ]
YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

39:08.179 --> 39:09.481
AND MADE YOU
SOME PAELLA.

39:09.515 --> 39:12.751
AND YOU
SAVED MY LIFE AGAIN.

39:12.784 --> 39:16.254
THANK YOU...
NEAL ARMSTRONG.

39:16.287 --> 39:19.190
NEAL ARMSTRONG --
DEFINITELY NOT REAL.

39:19.224 --> 39:20.692
YEAH,
KIND OF FIGURED.

39:25.697 --> 39:27.533
SURE MADE
FOR A GREAT STORY, THOUGH.

39:36.207 --> 39:39.010
WE MADE THE WINDOW

39:39.044 --> 39:41.580
FOR FORENSICS
TO TRACK THE BANK TRANSFER.

39:41.613 --> 39:43.114
MONEY'S BEEN RECOVERED,

39:43.148 --> 39:44.683
AND IT LOOKS LIKE
THEY CAN PROVE

39:44.716 --> 39:46.552
MAILER TAMPERED
WITH COVINGTON'S REGULATOR.

39:46.585 --> 39:47.986
WE CAN ALSO
GET HIM ON MURDER.

39:49.588 --> 39:50.722
HANDED YOU AN INCH,

39:50.756 --> 39:52.357
YOU SPRINTED
TO THE FINISH LINE.

39:52.390 --> 39:55.026
CAFFREY
DID THE SAME THING.

39:55.060 --> 39:56.628
THE TWO OF YOU...

39:57.596 --> 39:59.364
CAREFUL, PETER.

39:59.397 --> 40:01.066
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO WAKE UP ONE DAY

40:01.099 --> 40:03.735
AND NOT RECOGNIZE
YOURSELF.

40:10.275 --> 40:11.743
THEY MADE A DECISION?

40:13.344 --> 40:16.114
[ SIGHS ]

40:16.147 --> 40:19.217
"IT IS OUR RECOMMENDATION
THAT HE BE REINSTATED

40:19.250 --> 40:20.586
"AS SPECIAL AGENT IN CHARGE

40:20.619 --> 40:22.654
"OF THE MANHATTAN
WHITE-COLLAR DIVISION

40:22.688 --> 40:24.089
EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY."

40:24.122 --> 40:25.390
CONGRATULATIONS,
HONEY.

40:25.423 --> 40:26.958
THANKS.

40:26.992 --> 40:28.727
CONGRATS, PETER. IT'LL BE GOOD
TO HAVE YOU BACK IN THE OFFICE.

40:28.760 --> 40:30.962
AND WE'RE NOT JUST SAYING
THAT BECAUSE WE GET TO
HAND CAFFREY BACK TO YOU.

40:30.996 --> 40:32.898
[ LAUGHTER ]

40:32.931 --> 40:34.600
WELL, I WOULDN'T BE HERE
IF IT WEREN'T FOR ALL OF YOU.

40:34.633 --> 40:36.935
YOU MAKE ME
LOOK GOOD.

40:36.968 --> 40:38.403
TO PETER BURKE.

40:38.436 --> 40:40.338
THE MAN WE ALL WISH
WE COULD BE MORE LIKE.

40:40.371 --> 40:42.240
CHEERS!CHEERS!
CHEERS!CHEERS!

40:42.273 --> 40:43.975
[ LAUGHTER ]

40:44.009 --> 40:47.613
LET ME GET OVER HERE.
SHAKE MY BOSS'S HAND. YEAH.

40:47.646 --> 40:49.447
[ LAUGHS ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:49.481 --> 40:52.918
HEY.
MM.

40:52.951 --> 40:55.821
TEAM'S BACK TOGETHER
THE WAY IT SHOULD BE.

40:55.854 --> 40:57.455
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:57.489 --> 40:58.790
REFILL?

40:58.824 --> 41:00.358
YES,
LOTS TO CELEBRATE.

41:00.391 --> 41:01.960
PETER'S BACK.

41:01.993 --> 41:03.128
SOPHIE'S SAFE.

41:03.161 --> 41:05.196
AND YOU'RE MAD AT ME.

41:05.230 --> 41:07.966
COME ON. TRUTH.

41:07.999 --> 41:09.935
OH, NEAL, I WAS.

41:09.968 --> 41:10.836
YOU HAD A RIGHT.

41:10.869 --> 41:12.671
AFTER EVERYTHING
YOU DID FOR ME, I --

41:12.704 --> 41:14.506
NEAL,
IT'S NOT ABOUT YOU.

41:14.540 --> 41:16.708
THAT'S VERY MATURE.

41:16.742 --> 41:19.545
I TOLD YOU ABOUT EMILY.

41:19.578 --> 41:21.680
YOUR SISTER.

41:21.713 --> 41:23.549
ONE DAY, I'M YELLING AT HER
FOR BORROWING MY CLOTHES,

41:23.582 --> 41:25.784
AND THE NEXT --
SHE RAN AWAY.

41:25.817 --> 41:29.020
YOU LEAVING LIKE THAT --
IT OPENED UP SOME OLD WOUNDS.

41:29.054 --> 41:32.190
YOU KNOW,
SHE'S OUT THERE SOMEWHERE.

41:32.223 --> 41:34.660
I JUST WISH
I KNEW WHERE.

41:34.693 --> 41:37.195
YOU DESERVE TO KNOW.

41:37.228 --> 41:38.997
DON'T WE ALL?
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:44.670 --> 41:46.738
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

41:50.341 --> 41:52.944
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

42:05.023 --> 42:06.725
ELLEN!

42:06.758 --> 42:09.561
NO! I'M FAMILY!
I'M FAMILY!

42:09.595 --> 42:11.997
I'M FAMILY!
HEY.

42:12.030 --> 42:14.666
THEY FOUND ME.

42:14.700 --> 42:16.434
WHO?
WHO DID THIS TO YOU?

42:16.467 --> 42:18.737
TRUST SAM.

42:18.770 --> 42:21.006
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

42:21.039 --> 42:22.608
ALL RIGHT, SHE'S IN RESPIRATORY
ARREST! WE GOT TO GO!

42:22.641 --> 42:23.742
I WANT TO COME
WITH YOU.

42:23.775 --> 42:24.976
LET US DO OUR JOB,
OKAY?
